SIMPLE: trusty
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Trusty
<hw>Trust"y</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <amorph>[<pos>Compar.</pos>
<adjf>Trustier</adjf> <pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>superl.</pos>
<adjf>Trustiest</adjf>.]</amorph> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Admitting of being
safely trusted; justly deserving confidence; fit to be confided in;
trustworthy; reliable.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Your <qex>trusty</qex> and most valiant servitor.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Hence, not liable to fail; strong; firm.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>His <qex>trusty</qex> sword he called to his aid.</q>
<rj><qau>Spenser.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>Involving trust; <as>as, a <ex>trusty</ex>
business</as>.</def> <mark>[R.]</mark> <rj><au>Shak.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Truth</ent>⟦br⟧
